 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To Miss M— B.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">NO more sorrows, no more cares,</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Tune my lyre to chearful airs.</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Now so happy, now so gay,</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">'Tis for — this my lay.</l>
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">While the nymphs with pleasure twine,</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">With each flower that decks the spring,</l>
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">The gay garland for the brow,</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Few amongst them sweet as you;</l>
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">May the nymph for him design'd,</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Ever faithful, ever kind;</l>
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Sweet and chearful, may she be;</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Temper and good sense like thee.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
